links.title: Ultragenyx to build gene therapy manufacturing facility
links.description: Ultragenyx Pharmaceutical has announced that it plans to build a new large-scale gene therapy manufacturing facility in Bedford, Massachusetts, thus enabling in-house manufacturing of the Company's pipeline of clinical stage adeno-associated virus-based gene therapies, including DTX301 for ornithine transcarbamylase deficiency, DTX401 for glycogen storage disease type Ia, and UX701 for Wilson disease, as well as other preclinical programs.The planned Phase 1 facility will encompass 100,000 square feet will be able to support two independent manufacturing suites with a capacity of 30 runs per year.
